WEBVTT

00:02.002 --> 00:03.333
(Brush crunching)

00:03.334 --> 00:05.205
Hello?

00:05.206 --> 00:08.039
Hello. Is anybody there?

00:10.081 --> 00:11.211
Aah!

00:11.212 --> 00:13.012
(Laughs) Dude,
I totally had you.

00:13.013 --> 00:14.314
Jerk. You almost
gave me a heart attack.

00:14.315 --> 00:15.385
Sorry I'm late.

00:15.386 --> 00:17.247
My dad almost caught
me sneaking out.

00:17.248 --> 00:18.248
(Sighs)

00:18.249 --> 00:19.249
Forgive me?

00:19.250 --> 00:20.390
(Chuckles)

00:20.391 --> 00:23.223
(Tires screeching, clattering)

00:23.224 --> 00:24.254
Oh, my god.

00:24.255 --> 00:27.097
Run!

00:27.098 --> 00:28.199
(Grunts)

00:31.362 --> 00:34.234
(People speaking indistinctly)

00:34.235 --> 00:35.265
Hi, mom.

00:35.266 --> 00:38.037
Good morning, lace.

00:38.038 --> 00:39.369
(Todd) Hey.

00:39.370 --> 00:41.211
Ugh. Sorry about
the last-minute notice.

00:41.212 --> 00:44.074
I'll be done with my deposition
in time to get her after school.

00:44.075 --> 00:46.076
It... it is no problem.
Stop apologizing. Okay.

00:46.077 --> 00:47.277
I'm just happy to be here.

00:47.278 --> 00:48.419
(Chuckles)

00:53.224 --> 00:54.224
Morning, Megan.

00:54.225 --> 00:55.425
Kate.

00:55.426 --> 00:57.157
Bye.

00:57.158 --> 00:58.259
Bye, sweetie.

01:00.331 --> 01:02.262
So... (Sighs)

01:02.263 --> 01:04.194
Uh, you want to
get some breakfast?

01:04.195 --> 01:06.136
We still have a little time.

01:06.137 --> 01:07.267
I'd like to,

01:07.268 --> 01:09.399
but can you just drop me
off at the school library?

01:09.400 --> 01:11.341
I've got a test today
and I need to study.

01:11.342 --> 01:13.203
You didn't study last night?

01:13.204 --> 01:15.205
It's kinda hard to concentrate
at the house lately.

01:15.206 --> 01:18.248
The walls are, like, paper thin.

01:18.249 --> 01:20.280
Wait. (Chuckles)

01:20.281 --> 01:22.182
What are you saying?

01:22.183 --> 01:25.215
I'm saying, I can hear
the TV downstairs.

01:25.216 --> 01:27.157
What are you saying?

01:27.158 --> 01:29.159
Nothing. Nothin'. Just... mm.

01:29.160 --> 01:30.461
Nothing at all.

01:32.463 --> 01:35.295
(Whispers) Eww.

01:35.296 --> 01:39.169
(Emergency radio chatter)

01:39.170 --> 01:42.173
(Camera shutter clicking)

01:43.404 --> 01:45.435
Good morning, Peter.

01:45.436 --> 01:47.307
Good morning.

01:47.308 --> 01:49.108
What do we got?

01:49.109 --> 01:50.280
The car sailed over
the embankment

01:50.281 --> 01:51.381
just before 5:00 A.M.

01:51.382 --> 01:54.113
The victim's been identified
as Daniel Davidson.

01:54.114 --> 01:55.485
He lives not even
five minutes away.

01:55.486 --> 01:57.147
Who found him?

01:57.148 --> 01:59.249
Two teenagers snuck
out here this morning

01:59.250 --> 02:01.221
to sow their burgeoning oats.

02:01.222 --> 02:03.453
Lot of that going around lately.

02:03.454 --> 02:06.125
Oh, just not
with you, I take it.

02:06.126 --> 02:07.327
(Indistinct conversations)

02:07.328 --> 02:09.128
This fell out of the car

02:09.129 --> 02:11.331
when the medics opened the door.

02:11.332 --> 02:13.303
Another texting
and driving accident?

02:13.304 --> 02:15.165
(Mozart's "eine kleine
nachtmusik" playing)

02:15.166 --> 02:17.267
Oh, god. That's me.

02:17.268 --> 02:18.438
That is your ringtone?

02:18.439 --> 02:20.270
For my mother.

02:20.271 --> 02:23.173
I find the music soothes me
before the inevitable onslaught.

02:23.174 --> 02:24.174
(Music stops)

02:24.175 --> 02:25.215
Damn it. (Liquid splashes)

02:25.216 --> 02:27.146
(Emergency radio chatter)

02:27.147 --> 02:30.180
Is your paresthesia
acting up again?

02:30.181 --> 02:31.381
No. (Exhales)

02:31.382 --> 02:33.383
My mother is.

02:33.384 --> 02:36.186
(Radio chatter continues)

02:36.187 --> 02:37.527
(Man) We've got a
vehicle tech on the way...

02:37.528 --> 02:40.290
(Speaks indistinctly)

02:40.291 --> 02:42.332
(Camera shutter clicks)

02:42.333 --> 02:44.334
Call bud and Sam.

02:44.335 --> 02:46.196
(Morris) He already did.

02:46.197 --> 02:47.537
Ooh. Must be
something pretty juicy

02:47.538 --> 02:51.301
for you to want to call
homicide to a car accident.

02:51.302 --> 02:52.372
Maybe I just missed you.

02:52.373 --> 02:53.473
(Laughs)

02:53.474 --> 02:55.375
Okay.

02:55.376 --> 02:57.377
(Indistinct
conversations continue)

02:57.378 --> 02:59.509
(Exhales)

02:59.510 --> 03:01.511
We've got mud on his shoes

03:01.512 --> 03:04.484
but not on the
gas or brake pedal.

03:04.485 --> 03:05.555
That's weird,

03:05.556 --> 03:07.357
but not stop-the-presses weird.

03:07.358 --> 03:09.259
(Camera shutter clicks) Hmm.

03:09.260 --> 03:10.460
Seat belt's all twisted up.

03:10.461 --> 03:12.262
Seems kinda careless.

03:12.263 --> 03:13.323
Look at his arms and hands.

03:13.324 --> 03:14.524
There's no apparent
compression fractures.

03:14.525 --> 03:16.366
Which he would've gotten
if he'd have braced himself

03:16.367 --> 03:18.328
before the crash. Well,
maybe he was drunk.

03:18.329 --> 03:19.529
Check this out.

03:19.530 --> 03:22.332
Thermal burn from the air bag.

03:22.333 --> 03:24.274
Right in the center
of the forehead.

03:24.275 --> 03:26.205
He didn't turn
away before impact,

03:26.206 --> 03:28.408
which means, he was
probably unconscious.

03:28.409 --> 03:30.440
That's juicy enough for me.

03:30.441 --> 03:32.542
Somebody strapped
this guy into the car

03:32.543 --> 03:35.545
and pushed him over the edge.

03:35.546 --> 03:38.389
This was no accident.

03:45.225 --> 03:48.228
(Indistinct conversations)

03:51.332 --> 03:53.503
What are you up to over there?

03:53.504 --> 03:55.365
Ah, new equipment
coming in today.

03:55.366 --> 03:58.237
Gas chromatograph
mass spectrometer.

03:58.238 --> 04:00.239
I know what it is, but we
ain't getting a new one here.

04:00.240 --> 04:01.511
Yeah, we are. It's
on its way right now.

04:01.512 --> 04:04.314
Oh, no, ma'am. Those babies
cost over 100 grand a pop.

04:04.315 --> 04:06.576
That's my entire equipment
budget for the year.

04:06.577 --> 04:08.378
Mm-hmm, which is
why I spent months

04:08.379 --> 04:10.450
writing Grant proposals
and wining and dining

04:10.451 --> 04:12.382
every major
benefactor in Philly.

04:12.383 --> 04:14.484
No one is touching your budget.

04:14.485 --> 04:15.625
Huh.

04:15.626 --> 04:18.528
I'm glad somebody's in
bed with the right people.

04:18.529 --> 04:19.529
(Laughs)

04:19.530 --> 04:22.362
We all have our talents.

04:22.363 --> 04:24.294
What did she say?

04:24.295 --> 04:26.336
I didn't hear nothin'.

04:26.337 --> 04:27.367
Ethan.

04:27.368 --> 04:28.398
Yeah.

04:28.399 --> 04:29.469
Stop everything.

04:29.470 --> 04:31.301
I have something very
important for you to do.

04:31.302 --> 04:33.503
Really? Sure. What is it?

04:33.504 --> 04:34.604
Fix my cell phone.

04:34.605 --> 04:37.547
It fell into a puddle
at the crime scene.

04:37.548 --> 04:39.349
Uh, yeah.

04:39.350 --> 04:40.580
Thanks.

04:40.581 --> 04:42.452
So... (Sighs)

04:42.453 --> 04:44.283
What is your story?

04:44.284 --> 04:48.287
I did a rapid saliva
test. He wasn't drunk.

04:48.288 --> 04:50.661
Right. Cell phone. That's
what I should be doing.

04:53.564 --> 04:56.496
I see faint ligature marks...
(Camera shutter clicks)

04:56.497 --> 04:58.528
On...

04:58.529 --> 05:00.430
Both wrists... (Clicking)

05:00.431 --> 05:02.432
With a distinct pattern.

05:02.433 --> 05:04.404
No restraints were
found on scene.

05:04.405 --> 05:07.607
And two abrasions on the
posterior upper right arm,

05:07.608 --> 05:09.379
already healing.

05:09.380 --> 05:11.641
Also not from the
accident. (Clicking)

05:11.642 --> 05:12.682
But...

05:12.683 --> 05:15.615
(Clicks)

05:15.616 --> 05:17.517
Huh.

05:17.518 --> 05:19.689
A splinter.

05:19.690 --> 05:21.451
(Click)

05:21.452 --> 05:23.393
And it looks like it's
got white paint on it.

05:23.394 --> 05:24.524
(Blows air) Check
his left nostril.

05:24.525 --> 05:27.498
I think there's
something inside.

05:31.602 --> 05:33.463
Red cloth fibers?

05:33.464 --> 05:35.605
Maybe something was held
over his face to incapacitate him.

05:35.606 --> 05:36.666
Why tie him up?

05:36.667 --> 05:38.408
Good question.

05:38.409 --> 05:39.539
I gotta get a fiber analysis

05:39.540 --> 05:41.511
and a tox screen on
this guy right away.

05:41.512 --> 05:43.413
Ethan.

05:43.414 --> 05:45.415
(Object clatters) Uh, right.

05:45.416 --> 05:49.419
Do you want me to do that
before or after the cell phone?

05:49.420 --> 05:50.481
Before.

05:51.722 --> 05:55.485
Are you sure it was my Daniel?

05:55.486 --> 05:58.528
I'm very sorry, Mrs. Davidson.

05:58.529 --> 06:01.491
You mind telling us the last
time you saw your husband?

06:01.492 --> 06:04.694
When we went to bed
last night, around 11:00.

06:04.695 --> 06:07.366
But he was gone when
I got up this morning.

06:07.367 --> 06:08.738
You weren't surprised
when he wasn't there?

06:08.739 --> 06:10.670
No. He always went to work early

06:10.671 --> 06:12.472
to avoid the traffic.

06:12.473 --> 06:14.474
What'd your husband do?

06:14.475 --> 06:16.676
He was a c.P.A.

06:16.677 --> 06:20.379
Started at his firm the
day after our honeymoon.

06:20.380 --> 06:23.653
Going on 16 years.

06:23.654 --> 06:26.486
(Voice breaks) He was
always such a cautious driver.

06:26.487 --> 06:28.488
Mrs. Davidson,

06:28.489 --> 06:30.490
there's a strong possibility

06:30.491 --> 06:32.592
that someone
staged the accident.

06:32.593 --> 06:34.393
How can that be?

06:34.394 --> 06:35.625
Do you know of anyone

06:35.626 --> 06:37.396
who may have wanted
to hurt your husband?

06:37.397 --> 06:38.628
No.

06:38.629 --> 06:40.500
Everyone loved Daniel.

06:40.501 --> 06:43.503
All he ever did was work
hard to provide for us

06:43.504 --> 06:47.406
so we could have a
house like this and...

06:47.407 --> 06:49.408
"We're... we're all...
We're all living the dream,"

06:49.409 --> 06:51.411
he used to always say.

06:52.483 --> 06:54.413
(Crying) I'm sorry.

06:54.414 --> 06:56.447
I can't, uh...

06:57.748 --> 06:59.750
(Mrs. Davidson sniffles)

07:02.553 --> 07:05.556
(Engine whirring)

07:24.545 --> 07:27.548
(Skateboard wheels rattling)

07:36.527 --> 07:38.559
(Peter) Megan, what's wrong?

07:40.531 --> 07:43.793
I used to live on a
cul-De-sac like this.

07:43.794 --> 07:47.838
Nothing is ever what it seems.

07:51.642 --> 07:52.842
(Fabric snaps)

07:52.843 --> 07:55.606
♪♪♪

08:00.811 --> 08:02.712
I'm telling you,

08:02.713 --> 08:04.754
there's something
in the air around here.

08:04.755 --> 08:05.955
I can feel it.

08:05.956 --> 08:07.917
Well, that intuition
and about $7

08:07.918 --> 08:09.789
will get you a cup of coffee.

08:09.790 --> 08:11.621
Where do you get your coffee?

08:11.622 --> 08:12.892
Little bistro down the street.

08:12.893 --> 08:13.923
A bistro?

08:13.924 --> 08:15.625
Oh, come on.

08:15.626 --> 08:16.826
Let's go see if c.S.U.

08:16.827 --> 08:19.699
Has finished processing
the davidsons' car.

08:19.700 --> 08:21.731
And a cause of
death wouldn't hurt.

08:21.732 --> 08:23.833
I'm all over it, detective.

08:23.834 --> 08:25.835
That is, if you can
pry Peter away.

08:25.836 --> 08:27.637
(Car door closes)

08:27.638 --> 08:28.908
(Peter and woman
speaking indistinctly)

08:28.909 --> 08:30.911
(Engine turns over)

08:34.715 --> 08:39.649
(Peter speaking indistinctly)

08:39.650 --> 08:42.021
Thank you.

08:42.022 --> 08:45.855
(Giggles)

08:45.856 --> 08:47.827
What was that? What was what?

08:47.828 --> 08:50.730
(Sexy voice) Oh, your badge...

08:50.731 --> 08:53.863
So big, so powerful.

08:53.864 --> 08:55.004
You should use
that voice more often.

08:55.005 --> 08:56.005
Mm.

08:56.006 --> 08:57.938
(Laughs)

09:04.875 --> 09:06.946
Where are you going?

09:06.947 --> 09:10.050
That splinter in Daniel's arm...

09:12.853 --> 09:15.686
That's blood.

09:16.857 --> 09:18.858
Can I help you?

09:18.859 --> 09:21.861
Uh, Peter dunlop. We're with
the medical examiner's office.

09:21.862 --> 09:24.734
We're investigating the
murder of Daniel Davidson.

09:24.735 --> 09:26.836
Heard it was just a car crash.

09:26.837 --> 09:27.898
Well, you heard wrong.

09:29.069 --> 09:31.070
Now this fence is
on his property line.

09:31.071 --> 09:33.072
Would you care to
explain the blood?

09:33.073 --> 09:35.875
I got into a fight with
Daniel the other day.

09:35.876 --> 09:37.006
A fight about what?

09:37.007 --> 09:38.948
Son of a bitch poisoned my dog.

09:38.949 --> 09:40.049
Do you know that for a fact?

09:40.050 --> 09:41.711
He kept complaining that my dog

09:41.712 --> 09:42.882
was digging up his flower beds.

09:42.883 --> 09:44.984
Then suddenly,
skipper got real sick.

09:44.985 --> 09:46.956
Daniel denied it,

09:46.957 --> 09:48.988
but you do the math.
Where's the dog now?

09:48.989 --> 09:50.820
The vet put him down.

09:50.821 --> 09:52.822
My kids are devastated.

09:52.823 --> 09:54.994
So, yeah, next time I saw him,

09:54.995 --> 09:57.026
we got into it.

09:57.027 --> 09:59.769
But kill him?

09:59.770 --> 10:00.871
No.

10:02.773 --> 10:05.005
Do you mind?

10:11.742 --> 10:15.084
Curtis, have you seen Megan?
She's not answering her cell.

10:15.085 --> 10:16.916
She's out with
Peter, bud, and Sam.

10:16.917 --> 10:18.948
Would you just please let
her know... (Elevator bell dings)

10:18.949 --> 10:20.951
I need to speak
with her immediately?

10:25.856 --> 10:26.856
(Sighs)

10:26.857 --> 10:28.028
(Elevator bell dings)

10:29.860 --> 10:33.102
Hey. Kate was just looking
for you, head all full of steam.

10:33.103 --> 10:35.064
Ugh. Tell her I'm
on a murder case.

10:35.065 --> 10:37.767
Unh-unh. I watch telenovelas.

10:37.768 --> 10:39.939
You two ain't sticking
me in the middle.

10:39.940 --> 10:42.972
This story has a tragic
end with no survivors.

10:42.973 --> 10:44.814
(Indistinct conversations)

10:44.815 --> 10:46.946
(Morris) So c.S.U. Found
some fingertip impressions

10:46.947 --> 10:49.849
on the rear bumper
of the car, caked in dirt.

10:49.850 --> 10:50.950
Right where you
push a car off the road.

10:50.951 --> 10:52.852
Any Ridge detail?

10:52.853 --> 10:55.124
No, just a crosshatch pattern.
The killer probably wore gloves.

10:55.125 --> 10:57.126
But they also
found this fancy key

10:57.127 --> 10:59.058
lodged in the driver's seat.

10:59.059 --> 11:02.792
I'll do you one better.
Remember Daniel's cell phone?

11:02.793 --> 11:03.893
Yeah.

11:03.894 --> 11:05.835
There was an unsent text
message on the screen.

11:05.836 --> 11:08.037
Before he died, he typed out,

11:08.038 --> 11:09.999
"I have to say something."

11:10.000 --> 11:12.001
Who was he gonna send it to?

11:12.002 --> 11:14.944
Just comes up a
first name... "Vicki."

11:14.945 --> 11:16.005
And you traced the number?

11:16.006 --> 11:18.007
She's one of his neighbors.

11:18.008 --> 11:19.849
(Indistinct conversations)

11:19.850 --> 11:20.910
(School bell rings)

11:20.911 --> 11:23.083
(Indistinct conversations)

11:35.966 --> 11:37.026
(Woman speaks indistinctly)

11:37.027 --> 11:38.968
Kate?

11:38.969 --> 11:40.830
Lacey, what happened?
Are you okay?

11:40.831 --> 11:43.102
I-I got sick in class.
What are you doing here?

11:43.103 --> 11:46.936
Uh, your dad is in
court, and your mom is...

11:46.937 --> 11:49.980
I just want to go home.

11:57.217 --> 11:59.919
(Sighs)

11:59.920 --> 12:01.951
Oh, where have
you been, Casanova?

12:01.952 --> 12:03.192
You know, that woman
may have had information

12:03.193 --> 12:04.924
that was pertinent to the case.

12:04.925 --> 12:06.055
Stuck in her cleavage?

12:06.056 --> 12:07.126
(Laughs)

12:07.127 --> 12:08.958
You were flirting.

12:08.959 --> 12:10.159
I was just doing my job, Megan.

12:10.160 --> 12:12.001
Mm.

12:12.002 --> 12:14.003
You're the one who seems
to be fixated on sex lately.

12:14.004 --> 12:17.236
Maybe it's because my boss

12:17.237 --> 12:21.040
is having sleepovers
with my ex-husband

12:21.041 --> 12:23.072
in a house with
paper-thin walls.

12:23.073 --> 12:25.945
Okay, let's change
the subject, shall we?

12:25.946 --> 12:28.017
What was Daniel
Davidson's cause of death?

12:28.018 --> 12:31.981
Aortic transection due
to the impact of the crash.

12:31.982 --> 12:34.223
But I did find something
I didn't expect.

12:34.224 --> 12:35.885
What?

12:35.886 --> 12:37.256
The color of the brain is off,

12:37.257 --> 12:40.890
and the cortical surfaces are
mildly depressed bilaterally.

12:40.891 --> 12:43.032
He had a leukoencephalopathy.

12:43.033 --> 12:44.994
How'd he get that? Not sure.

12:44.995 --> 12:47.166
The insulation of the
nerves inside his brain

12:47.167 --> 12:49.238
was being destroyed.

12:49.239 --> 12:52.241
Given the demyelination,
it could be m.S.

12:52.242 --> 12:55.044
Or he could have a
polyomavirus infection,

12:55.045 --> 12:57.206
specifically a j.C. Virus.

12:57.207 --> 12:59.178
Doesn't that virus
only infect people

12:59.179 --> 13:01.951
with a weakened immune system?

13:01.952 --> 13:05.054
But Daniel has never
had an organ transplant.

13:05.055 --> 13:08.087
And he had no history
of hodgkin's or leukemia.

13:08.088 --> 13:09.989
There is one other possibility.

13:09.990 --> 13:11.020
(Splashes)

13:11.021 --> 13:14.194
He could be h.I.V. Positive.

13:19.099 --> 13:21.070
Vicki hemington?

13:21.071 --> 13:22.071
Yes.

13:22.072 --> 13:23.072
Bud Morris.

13:23.073 --> 13:24.203
Philly homicide.

13:24.204 --> 13:26.936
I'd like to ask you
a few questions

13:26.937 --> 13:28.307
about Daniel Davidson
if you don't mind.

13:28.308 --> 13:30.309
(Exhales) It's so
horrible, what happened.

13:30.310 --> 13:33.082
Daniel was such a great guy.

13:33.083 --> 13:36.085
Well, we think his accident
was a result of foul play.

13:36.086 --> 13:37.216
Really?

13:37.217 --> 13:40.089
Would you mind if we took
a look around, uh, inside?

13:40.090 --> 13:42.952
Oh, uh... no. Not at all.

13:42.953 --> 13:44.153
Yeah. Follow me.

13:44.154 --> 13:46.026
(Whispers) Sam.

13:55.205 --> 13:58.037
So tell me, Mrs. Hemington,

13:58.038 --> 14:00.169
did you know Daniel very well?

14:00.170 --> 14:03.042
As well as you can
know a neighbor, I guess.

14:03.043 --> 14:05.274
I know this is a
sensitive matter,

14:05.275 --> 14:07.146
but I have to ask.

14:07.147 --> 14:09.078
Were you two having an affair?

14:09.079 --> 14:10.279
(Man) A what?

14:10.280 --> 14:12.151
Bill, what are you doing home?

14:12.152 --> 14:14.023
Vicki, what the hell?

14:14.024 --> 14:16.025
I didn't know you were
coming home for lunch.

14:16.026 --> 14:18.027
Yeah, I guess not.
What's going on?

14:18.028 --> 14:19.228
Who are you?

14:19.229 --> 14:21.130
They're from the police
