So brave to still
make it out today.

27:29.048 --> 27:31.179
Just know...

27:31.180 --> 27:33.121
We are all grieving.

27:33.122 --> 27:34.322
Thank you. Yeah.

27:34.323 --> 27:36.124
You said to bring
friends, right?

27:36.125 --> 27:37.185
Mm-hmm.

27:37.186 --> 27:38.256
This is Megan.

27:38.257 --> 27:40.328
Ooh. So nice to
have you. Thank you.

27:40.329 --> 27:43.131
Ladies, please...
Make yourself at home.

27:43.132 --> 27:44.362
(Music continues)

27:44.363 --> 27:46.164
Thank you.

27:46.165 --> 27:49.167
(Music continues)

27:49.168 --> 27:50.438
(Bell tinkling) Ah, yes.

27:50.439 --> 27:53.141
Thank you. (Andrea,
singsongy) Ladies.

27:53.142 --> 27:56.404
(Chuckles) It is so great
to have you all here today.

27:56.405 --> 27:59.077
(Tinkles)

27:59.078 --> 28:02.410
As a sisterhood, we all
have something in common.

28:02.411 --> 28:07.255
We know an amazing
opportunity when it presents itself

28:07.256 --> 28:11.219
and also possess
the strength to seize it.

28:11.220 --> 28:12.220
(Sets glass down)

28:12.221 --> 28:13.291
Narantha island...

28:13.292 --> 28:15.393
This newly discovered gem

28:15.394 --> 28:19.127
has been untouched
by time or tourism.

28:19.128 --> 28:21.099
And for a small down payment,

28:21.100 --> 28:23.471
you can begin to own a piece

28:23.472 --> 28:26.474
of an all-inclusive community.

28:26.475 --> 28:29.107
I know I don't need
to give you a hard sell

28:29.108 --> 28:31.109
because the proof
is in the pudding.

28:31.110 --> 28:32.380
(Giggles)

28:32.381 --> 28:36.314
I'm giving each of you a
chance to invest in yourselves,

28:36.315 --> 28:38.346
in your own future,

28:38.347 --> 28:42.250
to stop being dependent
on your parents,

28:42.251 --> 28:44.322
your husbands,

28:44.323 --> 28:46.325
anyone. (Silverware
clanks against glass)

28:48.127 --> 28:49.497
Excuse me. Hi.

28:49.498 --> 28:51.229
Hello.

28:51.230 --> 28:52.400
Sorry.

28:52.401 --> 28:57.135
I am all for financial
independence

28:57.136 --> 28:58.336
but I think,

28:58.337 --> 29:01.269
first the sisterhood

29:01.270 --> 29:03.271
should first know
the ingredients

29:03.272 --> 29:05.413
in therealpudding.

29:05.414 --> 29:08.246
I had my friends at
the police department

29:08.247 --> 29:10.278
do a little research.

29:10.279 --> 29:13.281
And it turns out
that narantha island

29:13.282 --> 29:16.524
is not so much an island per se

29:16.525 --> 29:19.487
but a landfill
covered with topsoil.

29:19.488 --> 29:22.290
And as for being near Bermuda,

29:22.291 --> 29:24.332
it's actually...

29:24.333 --> 29:27.295
In the Bermuda triangle.

29:27.296 --> 29:30.198
I'm not saying that you'll
disappear if you go there,

29:30.199 --> 29:32.370
but your money certainly will.

29:32.371 --> 29:34.302
Guaranteed.

29:34.303 --> 29:36.444
I imagine you already
knew all that, didn't you?

29:36.445 --> 29:38.476
(Laughs) Are youkidding?

29:38.477 --> 29:40.308
Of course not.

29:40.309 --> 29:42.510
Oh. And what about
Daniel Davidson?

29:42.511 --> 29:44.452
He catch on to your scheme?

29:44.453 --> 29:46.354
That's enough. Get out.

29:46.355 --> 29:47.555
I'm gonna find out the truth.

29:47.556 --> 29:49.457
But until then,

29:49.458 --> 29:53.322
you're going to pay back
every cent you were given.

29:55.394 --> 29:56.464
(Sighs)

29:56.465 --> 29:59.227
(Indistinct conversations)

29:59.228 --> 30:00.398
I'm not sure when
I'll be off work.

30:00.399 --> 30:03.201
(Woman) No problem.

30:03.202 --> 30:05.373
You know, we should
go and grab a drink or...

30:05.374 --> 30:06.574
(Woman) Yeah.
Coffee or... i don't know.

30:06.575 --> 30:08.306
Yeah, let's do it. Peter.

30:08.307 --> 30:09.377
Anything. Huh?

30:09.378 --> 30:11.239
Uh...

30:11.240 --> 30:12.310
You better call me.

30:12.311 --> 30:14.213
I will. (Door closes)

30:16.285 --> 30:17.345
(Woman laughs)

30:17.346 --> 30:19.347
(Women speaking indistinctly)

30:19.348 --> 30:21.549
Wow. You certainly
know how to clear a room.

30:21.550 --> 30:23.491
Ugh. You wouldn't
believe it in there.

30:23.492 --> 30:25.293
What did Vicki say?

30:25.294 --> 30:27.295
It's not just her. It's
all of them. It's bizarre.

30:27.296 --> 30:29.297
I mean, i... Daniel's
just been murdered,

30:29.298 --> 30:31.329
and... and they act
like nothing's going on.

30:31.330 --> 30:33.361
This is really
affecting you, huh?

30:33.362 --> 30:35.233
What? I'm not crying.

30:35.234 --> 30:37.265
Yes, you are. (Chuckles)

30:37.266 --> 30:41.309
(Women continue
speaking indistinctly)

30:41.310 --> 30:43.371
Where's your kit?
You have your kit?

30:43.372 --> 30:45.373
(Sighs)

30:45.374 --> 30:47.615
What are you doing?

30:47.616 --> 30:50.448
Those vials are for
evidence, you know?

30:50.449 --> 30:52.420
Exactly.

30:52.421 --> 30:53.551
What, you honestly think

30:53.552 --> 30:56.324
the answer to solving
this case is in your tears?

30:56.325 --> 30:58.327
Actually, I do.

31:07.196 --> 31:08.396
I have to say, this
goes above and beyond

31:08.397 --> 31:10.198
even for you, doctor. (Sighs)

31:10.199 --> 31:12.300
Actually using taxpayer dollars

31:12.301 --> 31:13.441
to test your own tears

31:13.442 --> 31:15.303
just to disprove the
fact that you cried.

31:15.304 --> 31:16.504
I was not crying, detective.

31:16.505 --> 31:18.306
Believe me, you will
know when I'm crying.

31:18.307 --> 31:19.377
Uh-huh. Sure you weren't.

31:19.378 --> 31:21.349
Everyone of those
women at the presentation

31:21.350 --> 31:23.381
got all teary-eyed for
no reason whatsoever,

31:23.382 --> 31:24.452
and then I did.

31:24.453 --> 31:25.513
That's called being a woman.

31:25.514 --> 31:27.455
Scientists proved that
thousands of years ago.

31:27.456 --> 31:29.517
Oh! (Ethan) Hey.

31:29.518 --> 31:32.290
Here's the tox report
you ordered on your...

31:32.291 --> 31:35.463
Uh, lacrimal fluids.

31:35.464 --> 31:37.265
This can't be
right. It's negative.

31:37.266 --> 31:40.198
Can we go back to
solving a murder now?

31:40.199 --> 31:42.200
Ethan, could you please
get me a ph test strip

31:42.201 --> 31:43.431
and the collection vial?

31:43.432 --> 31:46.204
Right away.

31:46.205 --> 31:48.307
(Clears throat)

31:49.578 --> 31:51.410
This... this horse
is dead, you know?

32:03.322 --> 32:04.592
(Laughs) I knew it.

32:04.593 --> 32:06.354
That thing test insanity?

32:06.355 --> 32:09.397
It tests acidity.

32:09.398 --> 32:11.399
The normal ph of
human tears is around 7.

32:11.400 --> 32:12.530
Mine is at a 4,

32:12.531 --> 32:15.303
which means that everyone
at the hemington house

32:15.304 --> 32:18.536
was exposed to a
volatile acidic compound

32:18.537 --> 32:21.469
which affected all of
our mucus membranes.

32:21.470 --> 32:27.375
I need to see the slides
of Daniel Davidson's brain.

32:27.376 --> 32:31.449
It turns out, there actually
is something in the air.

32:31.450 --> 32:33.551
Ah. So...

32:33.552 --> 32:35.553
Daniel did have
spongiform regions

32:35.554 --> 32:37.425
in his subcortical white matter,

32:37.426 --> 32:39.427
which means he was suffering
from a leukoencephalopathy

32:39.428 --> 32:40.628
like I thought,

32:40.629 --> 32:42.430
but this was toxin-induced.

32:42.431 --> 32:43.591
Toxin-induced?

32:43.592 --> 32:46.294
Like from the brake cleaner
he was incapacitated with?

32:46.295 --> 32:47.465
No, that was an acute exposure.

32:47.466 --> 32:48.596
This would be chronic.

32:48.597 --> 32:51.469
Absorbed over a
period of months maybe.

32:51.470 --> 32:53.471
So what was he exposed to?

32:53.472 --> 32:55.473
(Sighs) We'll have to check
his liver and blood to find out,

32:55.474 --> 32:57.475
and that is not a
normal tox report.

32:57.476 --> 32:59.477
Farming it out is
gonna take days.

32:59.478 --> 33:02.380
No, it won't. Why don't we
just use our new mass spec?

33:02.381 --> 33:05.313
You're funny. Oh, my god. Do I
know something that you don't know?

33:05.314 --> 33:06.514
(Laughs) We don't
have a new mass spec.

33:06.515 --> 33:08.356
Yes, we do have a new mass spec.

33:08.357 --> 33:10.358
It was delivered
yesterday. It was set up.

33:10.359 --> 33:13.392
It's ready to go. Dr. Kate
Murphy to the rescue.

33:15.664 --> 33:18.367
Huh.

33:20.369 --> 33:22.370
Hi, lace. It's me again.

33:22.371 --> 33:23.571
I hope you're feeling better.

33:23.572 --> 33:25.373
And I hope you know

33:25.374 --> 33:28.476
that I wasn't avoiding
your calls yesterday.

33:28.477 --> 33:31.639
I'm gonna come
by after work, okay?

33:31.640 --> 33:34.482
Love you.

33:34.483 --> 33:36.384
(Knock on door)

33:36.385 --> 33:37.616
This a bad time?

33:48.697 --> 33:51.459
When Lacey was 7,

33:51.460 --> 33:53.661
she got these
skates that she loved.

33:53.662 --> 33:55.603
She used to...

33:55.604 --> 33:57.605
Go up and down
the street for hours.

33:57.606 --> 33:59.607
I'd watch her.

33:59.608 --> 34:01.569
And one day she, um...

34:01.570 --> 34:05.473
She hit a rock, she tripped,
and she skinned her knees.

34:05.474 --> 34:07.645
I carried her into the
house, fixed her up,

34:07.646 --> 34:11.550
and just held her
until she calmed down.

34:13.352 --> 34:16.524
And she looked up at me...

34:16.525 --> 34:18.557
Smiled...

34:20.589 --> 34:24.562
And I felt something that
I had never felt before.

34:24.563 --> 34:26.695
I was her hero.

34:29.538 --> 34:32.571
I've done nothing but
disappoint her ever since.

34:36.375 --> 34:38.406
Yesterday, you were her hero.

34:38.407 --> 34:41.609
Megan, Todd asked for my
help and I gave it. That's all.

34:41.610 --> 34:44.412
And I tried to get ahold
of you numerous times.

34:44.413 --> 34:46.384
My phone was broken.
You... you could've tried Peter.

34:46.385 --> 34:48.416
You know, I have
a job to do, too.

34:48.417 --> 34:50.418
And if you think for a minute
that I want to get in the middle

34:50.419 --> 34:52.520
of whatever family drama
you've got on tap for the day...

34:52.521 --> 34:54.462
Come on. That is not fair.

34:54.463 --> 34:56.464
No, what's not fair is you
playing me off as a bad guy

34:56.465 --> 34:57.695
for helping your daughter

34:57.696 --> 35:00.698
just because you're desperate
to buy back a moment with her.

35:00.699 --> 35:02.500
All right? It's not
my responsibility.

35:02.501 --> 35:04.702
Okay? It's yours.

35:04.703 --> 35:08.536
I'm telling you, telenovelas,
ain't no survivors.

35:08.537 --> 35:10.438
What is it, Curtis?

35:10.439 --> 35:12.680
Got the report you needed
from the new mass spec...

35:12.681 --> 35:16.414
Daniel Davidson's
liver and blood.

35:16.415 --> 35:18.416
There's definitely a toxin
running through his system.

35:18.417 --> 35:20.418
There's a spike in the
area of the volatiles,

35:20.419 --> 35:23.421
characteristic of...

35:23.422 --> 35:24.522
Toluene.

35:24.523 --> 35:25.693
That's a hydrocarbon.

35:25.694 --> 35:27.425
Nasty stuff.

35:27.426 --> 35:30.658
Found in gasoline, acrylics,
and paint thinners among others.

35:30.659 --> 35:32.700
So Daniel was suffering
from toluene toxicity.

35:32.701 --> 35:35.503
That is what caused
the leukoencephalopathy.

35:35.504 --> 35:38.807
That whole neighborhood
is being exposed to poison.

35:40.539 --> 35:43.512
And it could be
killing all of them.

35:48.146 --> 35:50.618
(Sirens wailing)

35:50.619 --> 35:52.680
(Tires squealing)

35:52.681 --> 35:53.881
(Wailing continues)

35:53.882 --> 35:55.683
(Police radio chatter)

35:55.684 --> 35:57.755
Fan out! Fan out!

35:57.756 --> 36:01.158
We need to evacuate every
single house in this neighborhood.

36:01.159 --> 36:02.830
And until we find the
source of those chemicals,

36:02.831 --> 36:05.162
proceed with caution.

36:05.163 --> 36:08.766
(Wailing continues)

36:08.767 --> 36:12.169
(Man) Take your
team around back!

36:12.170 --> 36:14.772
(Man) Somebody
knock on this door.

36:14.773 --> 36:16.704
(Man) And I got a guest house.

36:16.705 --> 36:18.906
(Police radio chatter)

36:18.907 --> 36:21.209
Mr. Kaiser.

36:21.210 --> 36:22.880
(Radio chatter continues)

36:22.881 --> 36:25.853
(Officers shouting indistinctly)

36:25.854 --> 36:27.655
Philly pd.

36:27.656 --> 36:28.786
(Man) Check the garage.

36:28.787 --> 36:30.758
(Man) And across the street!

36:30.759 --> 36:32.860
(Morris) Anybody home?

36:32.861 --> 36:34.722
Hey, bud. What?

36:34.723 --> 36:37.665
Look at these flowers in front.

36:37.666 --> 36:38.766
Yeah?

36:38.767 --> 36:40.668
Yeah, now check out
these over on the side.

36:40.669 --> 36:43.731
They're the exact same
flowers, but they're turning green.

36:43.732 --> 36:45.233
They're a different color. So?

36:45.234 --> 36:47.235
When anhydrous ammonia
escapes into the air,

36:47.236 --> 36:48.976
it can change the
color of flowers to green.

36:48.977 --> 36:50.978
Somebody's cooking
meth around here.

36:50.979 --> 36:54.943
That's what the neighbors
have been breathing in.

36:56.785 --> 36:58.886
(Man) All right. Let's go!

36:58.887 --> 37:00.988
(Police radio chatter)

37:00.989 --> 37:04.723
(Officers shouting indistinctly)

37:15.834 --> 37:16.964
Philly pd!

37:16.965 --> 37:18.766
Hands in the air, kaiser.

37:18.767 --> 37:20.007
In the air. Higher.

37:20.008 --> 37:22.940
Get on your knees. Lace
your hands behind your head.

37:22.941 --> 37:24.973
Get on your knees! Now!

37:27.776 --> 37:29.817
We found the red
shop towel you used

37:29.818 --> 37:31.018
to incapacitate Daniel Davidson.

37:31.019 --> 37:32.820
And the pattern on your gloves

37:32.821 --> 37:35.953
matches the ones we found
on the rear bumper of his car.

37:35.954 --> 37:38.827
It's time to come clean, Kevin.

37:41.760 --> 37:43.732
(Grunts)

37:44.993 --> 37:47.035
I, um...

37:50.268 --> 37:52.800
I lost my job a year ago.

37:52.801 --> 37:54.842
And, uh...

37:54.843 --> 37:56.043
(Inhales deeply)

37:56.044 --> 37:59.307
(Exhales) I couldn't
get hired anywhere.

37:59.308 --> 38:02.950
We were deep in
debt, and I just...

38:02.951 --> 38:04.011
(Sighs)

38:04.012 --> 38:06.283
Unraveled.

38:06.284 --> 38:08.956
Quite a leap to
meth manufacturing.

38:08.957 --> 38:11.889
One of my cousins
used to be a dealer.

38:11.890 --> 38:13.891
He told me I could get
out of the hole I was in

38:13.892 --> 38:16.293
by cooking meth.

38:16.294 --> 38:20.768
I thought maybe if I
could right myself, I...

38:20.769 --> 38:22.930
I could get things back
to the way they used to be.

38:22.931 --> 38:25.032
How did Daniel find out?

38:25.033 --> 38:27.034
It was so early in the morning,

38:27.035 --> 38:30.037
i-i... I never expected
anyone to hear me.

38:30.038 --> 38:32.780
But he was coming
home from Vicki's house.

38:32.781 --> 38:35.012
Suddenly, he was
just there in the shed,

38:35.013 --> 38:37.314
asking me what
the hell I was doing.

38:37.315 --> 38:39.847
Are you aware that

38:39.848 --> 38:41.989
the waste product
from your meth lab

38:41.990 --> 38:44.051
has contaminated
the air and soil

38:44.052 --> 38:45.993
of the entire neighborhood?

38:45.994 --> 38:48.796
It's already killed
your neighbor's dog.

38:48.797 --> 38:50.898
If Daniel hadn't found out...

38:50.899 --> 38:54.002
How many people
would've been next?

38:55.804 --> 38:59.907
So you got the drop on
Daniel with the shop cloth and...

38:59.908 --> 39:02.911
I, um...

39:06.845 --> 39:09.076
I took his car out
into the woods,

39:09.077 --> 39:12.079
and, um...

39:12.080 --> 39:15.023
I pushed it over.

39:16.955 --> 39:19.127
(Voice breaks) I just, uh...

39:21.059 --> 39:22.860
(Sniffles)

39:22.861 --> 39:25.092
(Exhales)

39:25.093 --> 39:29.367
I couldn't have anything
else taken away from me.

39:35.944 --> 39:39.376
(Indistinct conversations)

39:39.377 --> 39:42.149
Oh-ho. I just heard. A meth lab?

39:42.150 --> 39:43.951
What do you want, Ethan?

39:43.952 --> 39:45.953
Well, if you're going
back to the police station,

39:45.954 --> 39:47.154
could you return these for me?

39:47.155 --> 39:48.155
Oh.

39:48.156 --> 39:49.417
Ooh. (Laughs)

39:49.418 --> 39:50.888
(Elevator bell dings)

39:50.889 --> 39:52.420
You might want to hold
on to that one. (Purrs)

39:52.421 --> 39:54.121
(Peter) No, I don't
bust out the toys

39:54.122 --> 39:56.123
until, you know,
the second date.

39:56.124 --> 39:57.865
(Chuckles)

39:57.866 --> 39:59.997
Ohh.

39:59.998 --> 40:03.100
(Clenched teeth) I thought
you were being professional.

40:03.101 --> 40:06.133
I am, but now it's personal.

40:06.134 --> 40:07.875
(Indistinct
conversations continue)

40:07.876 --> 40:10.137
Any houses for rent
in this cul-De-sac?

40:10.138 --> 40:14.141
(Normal voice) You couldn't
handle a desperate housewife.

40:14.142 --> 40:16.944
Believe me.

40:16.945 --> 40:19.147
(Indistinct
conversations continue)

40:20.418 --> 40:22.019
(Knock on door)

40:22.020 --> 40:23.922
Come in.

40:26.955 --> 40:29.197
Mom. Hi.

40:31.099 --> 40:32.900
How you feelin'?

40:32.901 --> 40:34.202
I'm... better.

40:36.064 --> 40:38.135
I hope you know that,
um... (Clicks tongue)

40:38.136 --> 40:40.037
I would have done anything

40:40.038 --> 40:41.438
to have been able to
pick you up yesterday.

40:41.439 --> 40:43.941
I just... I hope you
know that... It's okay.

40:43.942 --> 40:45.943
'Cause I-I meant
what I said to your dad,

40:45.944 --> 40:48.916
that i'm... I'm
happy to be here,

40:48.917 --> 40:51.218
and... and not just for, uh,
shopping and movies and...

40:51.219 --> 40:53.220
I mean, that's all great, but...

40:53.221 --> 40:54.482
Mom.

40:54.483 --> 40:57.125
I know. I promise.

40:59.057 --> 41:00.929
Look, it's my own fault anyway.

41:02.190 --> 41:08.196
I mean, I probably just...
Something I ate or whatever.

41:12.000 --> 41:14.041
You weren't sick, were you?

41:14.042 --> 41:17.074
What? Yeah.

41:17.075 --> 41:20.007
I...

41:20.008 --> 41:21.078
How did you know?

41:21.079 --> 41:23.080
(Laughs)

41:23.081 --> 41:25.152
Uh...

41:25.153 --> 41:28.016
Because I'm your mother.

41:29.157 --> 41:31.218
Wow.

41:31.219 --> 41:33.120
That is beautiful.

41:33.121 --> 41:35.523
Did you do this?

41:35.524 --> 41:37.024
Yeah.

41:37.025 --> 41:38.526
Wow.

41:38.527 --> 41:40.998
I love art.

41:40.999 --> 41:42.499
♪♪♪

41:42.500 --> 41:45.132
So why'd you lie?

41:45.133 --> 41:46.974
Hmm?

41:46.975 --> 41:49.276
♪♪♪

41:49.277 --> 41:51.278
I didn't want to have
to take my science test

41:51.279 --> 41:53.981
because I knew I
was going to fail.

41:53.982 --> 41:55.042
♪♪♪

41:55.043 --> 41:59.186
I just don't get it.

41:59.187 --> 42:02.189
I know how much
you love science...

42:02.190 --> 42:05.192
And I didn't want
to disappoint you.

42:05.193 --> 42:09.256
♪♪♪

42:09.257 --> 42:11.258
(Chuckles)

42:11.259 --> 42:12.529
(Sighs)

42:12.530 --> 42:15.032
You know what, lace?

42:15.033 --> 42:16.533
(Woman) ♪ la la la la ♪

